The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a meeting with North Korean defectors in Seoul, South Korea. Pence expressed gratitude for their courage and shared his support for their cause of freedom. He also mentioned the harsh conditions faced by North Koreans, including labor camps and food shortages. Fred Warmbier, whose son Otto Warmbier was imprisoned in North Korea and later died, also spoke at the meeting. Four defectors shared their personal stories of escaping North Korea and the hardships they faced. Pence emphasized the importance of sharing the truth about the North Korean regime, which he described as a cruel dictatorship.